\title{Guidelines for contributors}

\p{We welcome a broader range of contributions, despite the name of the
project. Both in related areas of \em{synthetic} mathematics, such as domain
theory or algebraic geometry; but also formalisations in the general theory of
HoTT. In order to formalise these synthetic mathematics it is important to have
a strong and well designed library of results in HoTT (including in
\em{set-level} mathematics). If you are unsure about what contributions would be
welcome, feel free to ask us on our [Discord
server](https://discord.gg/Jfxv4jPTva).}

\p{Concepts should be contained within their own subtrees, with an appropriate
taxonomy, and in all but the most simple cases should come with an informal
mathematical description of the lemma/definition/theorem, as well as a sketched
informal proof if appropriate.}

\p{We maintain that the informal content is of \em{equal importance} to the
formal content, i.e., Agda code. Consequently, we also welcome contributions
that only contain \em{partial} formalisations, i.e., where select results are
only defined or proved informally without accompanying Agda code.}


